{
  "final_answer": "## Starshield Segment Classification and Revenue Disclosure\n\n### Glossary Definition\nThe S-1 defines **Starshield** as a secure satellite network designed specifically for government customers and national security applications. It is built on Starlink's infrastructure and focuses on three core mission areas: Earth observation, global secure communications, and hosted payloads, with high-assurance cryptographic capabilities tailored for military and government requirements.\n\n### Reporting Segment\nStarshield revenue is included in the **Connectivity segment**, one of the company's three reporting segments (Space, Connectivity, AI). More specifically, Starshield revenue falls within the **\"Enterprise & Government\"** sub-category of the Connectivity segment's disaggregated revenue presentation.\n\n### Revenue Contribution Disclosure\n**The filing does not provide a specific, standalone revenue figure, percentage, or quantified contribution for Starshield.** Starshield revenue is aggregated into the broader \"Enterprise & Government\" line within the Connectivity segment. For context:\n\n- In fiscal year 2025, the **Connectivity segment** reported total revenue of **$11,387 million**, of which:\n  - Consumer revenue: $7,208 million\n  - **Enterprise & Government revenue (includes Starshield): $4,179 million**\n\nThe filing does note that government connectivity revenue (which encompasses Starshield) increased by approximately $1,250 million in FY 2024, but it does not isolate how much of that increase (or of total Enterprise & Government revenue) is attributable specifically to Starshield.\n\n### Revenue Recognition\nStarshield contracts are multi-year in nature and recognized over time using the **cost-to-cost input method** under ASC 606, reflecting the long-term contract nature of government satellite network engagements.\n\n**In summary:** Starshield is part of the Connectivity segment's Enterprise & Government sub-category, but the filing provides no disaggregated disclosure of Starshield's specific revenue contribution — only the combined Enterprise & Government figure is reported.",
